link.to.the.model.com: Example Boolean model of NF-κB signaling pathway
Li, Luna, "Center for Reproducible Biomedical Modeling, University of Washington", lixy@uw.edu
Niarakis, Anna, "Laboratoire Européen de Recherche Pour La Polyarthrite Rhumatoïde, University Paris-Saclay, University Evry", anna.niarakis@inria.fr
Gennari, John, "Center for Reproducible Biomedical Modeling, University of Washington", gennari@uw.edu

This is a toy example to demonstrate the standardized spreadsheet format for logical models.
This Boolean model represents a core regulatory motif in the NF-κB signaling pathway, focusing on the formation and activation of the NF-κB transcriptional complex (C) driven by external stimuli (D) and its effect on downstream cytokine expression (E).
Another example of a multi-valued version of the model is provided as ToyExample_multivalue.xlsx.
